tip.text: Lamb chops, mezze, fish grill and fried cauliflower
Blacken fish with the curried pumpkin fries. My favourite here now by far!
Great idea to have guest chefs cooking from different regions. So today I stuck to the borscht soup which was really authentic
The chicken burger in lettuce leaf was amazing but the star of the show was the raw pumpkin cake special! This place is great for health👍
The chicken was crispy and tasty but next time I'll try something different to this platter!
I like that I can get a good soya matcha but I suppose the bread is good quality

location.address: 44 Jalan Merah Saga, #01-56 Chip Bee Gardens
formattedAddress: 44 Jalan Merah Saga, #01-56 Chip Bee Gardens

tip.text: Great outdoor feel & quality food. But small portions!
Where better to enjoy a proper roast & the best English puddings. Including apple & crumble!
The churros of course! Love the chocolate but I prefer a doughy churros. It was very crispy.

formattedAddress: C. Pasadizo de San Ginés, 5 (C. Arenal)

tip.text: Palak paneer, black lentil Dahl & veggies
Great quality sushi with lovely takeaway options. This will become my new go to for lunch or post work at raffles!
We got a selection of the tapas. The gambas (prawns) is a must, not enough meaty pork in the croquettas but realised pleased overall with the authenticity of the food! I'll try the beef next time
Healthy vegetarian food with a wide range that could even satisfy meat eaters
Loved this beet (millet) burger which I added sunny side egg. The hot cacao was also really nice too but service is a little slow.
Extremely well cooked & beautiful food. The short ribs for restaurant week were amazing! Slowly braised so it fell off the bone, the puddings were to die for, chocolate moose with cashew nut crunch!
Good value set menu $11ish although could have been more flexible than just the fried spring roll as the starter option. The pho was good though!
The fish tasted like frozen fish cooked so not as fresh as would have liked & was glad to have asked for the sauce on the side, would probably stick more to meat here!
Yeah!!!Restaurant week so back to one of my favs. Lovely slap of fish or the lamb Ragu pasta

formattedAddress: Lv 43, Ocean Financial Centre (10 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: It's my favourite Korean BBQ so far, non greasy seafood pancake, spicy pork & good atmostphere

venue.name: 왕대박 Wang Dae Bak Korean BBQ Restaurant

tip.text: You must try the deconstructed omelette for an unforgettable way of trying Spanish omelette. It's pricey here but the food is just great. Just need bigger portions!
This place deserves so many ratings, breakfast, brunch & dinner. I'm addicted to their fries!
We chose well with seafood done chilli sauce style, steam fish & veggies but I wouldn't come out of my way to go here the service inevitably let it down

formattedAddress: #01-05, East Coast Parkway Seafood Centre (Blk 1204 East Coast Parkway)

tip.text: It's brilliant value, good portions & great for sharing. Get their North Indian inspired platters, samosas and don't try the spicy Mexican beer!
Great selection of fish & seafood done in most styles. Happy hour deals are good too and it's all about the views here!
Impressive brunch menu, muesli jars, fresh juices, fusion dishes & i did see a good cocktail menu for later. Quirky decorated place but a must!
Good choice of steaks and well paired sides like beetroot & grilled asparagus. Always with limoncello of course!
The selection of American spirits & mixers, the knowledgeable staff and the tucked away site! I love the organic rum.

formattedAddress: B1-08, Ocean Financial Centre (10 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: It's an Aussie brunch hangout & it's does it well, healthy breakfast, good coffee, teas & some deli shopping whilst there!
I love the cocktail selection here,  ladies night is great for fizz n oysters, plus check out their sliders!
The platters with a good meat & seafood selection and the cocktail list was impressive. Tables upstairs with lovely views made this a lovely lazy afternoon with art thrown in!
Friends took us and the chef insisted on showing us simple good quality Italian food cooked well...he was right & we will be back for beef & truffles!
Client lunches, girls catchup here are great with the massive selection of teas & petit cakes

Unsurprisingly the cocktails & choice of rum is amazing. Very low key feel but the music & clean but tasty food to suit most tastes looking for western food with friends, typical Friday night venture!
Nice catch up place with friends, ok tapas & wine. Didn't blow me away with flavours but equally didn't go to wrong! Would go with the girls to suit all tastes

formattedAddress: 14 Ann Siang Road (Ann Siang Road / Club Street)

tip.text: This place will really keep groups happy with the quality & selection of food! Champagne brunch has Verve cliquot & 1 of my favourite red wines - McGuigan from Australia
Good quality meat and healthy sides. I wish this place was on my doorstep for my postwork out meals!
I love this place, healthy salads with good protein, quinoa & homemade dressings.
The staff the service and the food. Although when I order tapas I have to order a lot to be full & at these prices not ideal! My go to place for amazing cocktails on ladies night though!
Breakfast with healthy options like porridge or their protein pots. Too pricey for salads for me although they are also popular there.
The service is brilliant they try to cover a combination of Indian food from North & South Indian & the concept of barefoot/cushion on the floor seating works. All dishes are very nicely cooked!
I love this Cobb salad! I hate paying more than $12 for a salad but the portion size complete with garlic bread & creamy blue cheese inside is worth it. Good find!
My pre or post workout protein meal! It's all about a good portion of chicken here with salad sides. I'm also a fan that they do Illy coffee here, I've noticed the pork shank goes down well too!
Marco is truely passionate about good Italian food & is knocking out high quality tasty home cooked creations but the short rib beef is to die for!

formattedAddress: Lv 43, Ocean Financial Centre (10 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: The seafood platter!! Seabass, squid & huge prawns BBQ'd. Very good seafood pancake, it's currently my best seafood restaurant in SG
Great brunch and rye bread! I also love the staff and good coffee!
Teas, coffees and laid back music. Very chilled place but has a champagne brunch venue too!
I asked for extra salmon at the Japanese to get a healthy option!

formattedAddress: 1 Vista Exchange Green (next to Buona Vista MRT)

tip.text: It's just good ramen, they do great free sides though too eggs, mashed potato & beansprouts. I can't bring myself to queue but would always go if no queue!
Took me off guard, I was not expecting such good seafood. The seafood platter the pancake and the mixed vegetables! They also do a good range of herbal & flower teas.
Healthy option I asked for a the Japanese in the top floor food court

formattedAddress: 1 Vista Exchange Green (next to Buona Vista MRT)

tip.text: Brunch, salads and desserts

formattedAddress: 45 Ann Siang Hill #02-02 (Ann Siang Hill Park)

tip.text: Joins my top 3 for best espresso martini. Good range of coffees & cocktails, puddings looked comforting. Nice for catch up drinks!
So it's not gonna be the best sushi you've had - but of course not at this price! Mackerel bento box is good, will ask for no dressings on the salad next time as a bit heavy handed
Loved this healthy fish soup, big chunky pieces, they were happy to do extra veggie & brown rice. They also do a meat or seafood option or with noodles. Such good value!
Newly open posh Indian. I loved it! Good Indian favourites like butter chicken, some healthy chai teas & nice chicken tikka. They had a very good value 3 course set lunch too!
The setting is really nice, staff are great & the food is very good quality well cooked Italian, they also have a great wine & cheese selection!
Food is just fine. Setting is the best bit about this place, but when you get the food order wrong 3 times, then the bill wrong it just ruins it all! Juice was the best bit!
Absolutely loved this superfood salad. One of the best salads I have ever had with green apple, kiwi & cucumber juice. Great if you want a healthy vegetarian option!

formattedAddress: 45 Ann Siang Hill #02-02 (Ann Siang Hill Park)

tip.text: Run of the mill Japanese. Fine for quick lunch, could have done with more creativity in the menu. Everything tasted fresh though but $30 for a set lunch all in isn't good value for their offerings
Try everything. What better way to have dim sum!! I always get a selection of dumplings (xiao long bao of course), sweet & sour soup & the seafood pancake. Love it!

formattedAddress: #B2-63, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands (2 Bayfront Ave)
location.address: #B2-63, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

tip.text: This is my must go to place when I have visitors for cocktails on the balcony and the must see view of Singapore! Justin Quek is so lovely too when he is around!

formattedAddress: Level 57 Sands SkyPark, Marina Bay Sands Hotel Tower 1 (10 Bayfront Ave.)
location.address: Level 57 Sands SkyPark, Marina Bay Sands Hotel Tower 1

tip.text: I took a friend here to try real Spanish food. Pleased with a selection of the dishes but not all so authentic. They do really take pride in the way the food is cooked & presented so I will be back!
The rooftop pool, the views, the luxury, the snacks and I will be back for what sounds like a brilliant ladies night on Wednesdays!
Really pleased with this! Lots of healthy options, flexible with my no wheat, no dairy week & attentive staff

formattedAddress: #02-20 The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)

tip.text: Loved my blue swimmer crab & prawn omelette, let's face it the place is great, the food is brill, the truffles fries a must, just a shame it's so pricey!
Baked eggs, matcha latte & decent coffees. Nice chilled atmosphere with a quirky indoor/outdoor setting.
Tried the eggs Benedict & was disappointed, when asked for spinach I was given oily iceberg lettuce. Next time I'll have the granola again which was amazing!

location.crossStreet: Corner of Teo Hong Rd. and New Bridge Rd.
formattedAddress: 331 New Bridge Rd. #01-02. (Corner of Teo Hong Rd. and New Bridge Rd.)

tip.text: Ladies night & posh boozing!
Truffle fries & wagu sliders everytime! My best view of Singapore

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Bay Hotel (80 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: The bartenders & the cocktails. They know their stuff & treat it like an art. Try espresso martinis & ladies night
I always love this spring chicken. The only down to this place is the portion size for the price is all a bit wrong. Tiramsu is a must here!
The chef is doing an amazing job of Italian & Spanish cuisine & happy to show flexibility for big groups making paellas
The coffee is great & the staff extremely friendly. You can't go wrong with any of the food especially breakfast!

Was disappointed at 1st when I saw the potatoes diced so small but the flavours were perfect. I love the brave amount of garlic in their food and they have managed to keep their churros light & fluffy
